$ vim option: cindent
@ cindent

If → development/vim/options/indentexpr[`indentexpr`] is not empty, then setting `cindent` starts automatic C-like → development/vim/editing/indent[indenting]

`cinkeys` contains the keys that trigger reindenting in insert mode.

`cinoptions` specify the indent style.

`cindent` is without effect when → development/vim/options/paste[`paste`] is set.

Setting the → development/vim/options/compatible[`compatible`] option resets `cindent`.

sa:

  → development/vim/options

  → development/vim/editing/indent
